From 9048bc25b3185ee20e79fe2fc202aeefdc59da2a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cryptohakka <noreply@local>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 05:14:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): min-episode guard so degenerate small-n cells
 can't false-positive

A horizon truncated to a couple of episodes (e.g. synthetic-leak 24h HIGH, nEp=2)
produced an explosive t-stat (t=375) off near-zero variance. Such cells are now
excluded from multiple-comparison and the verdict when nEpisodes < --min-episodes
(default 5); they are still reported under multiple_comparison.underpowered_excluded.

- engine: tested-cell partition drives M, BH, Bonferroni, min_p and power
- verdict/index: expose min_episodes + underpowered_excluded; mark excluded cells in
  the human summary; add --min-episodes flag (forwarded to selfcheck too)
- test: assert the guard plumbing (M=0 at impossibly high min; real edge still SURVIVES)
- examples: regenerate outputs/selfcheck (perceptrade NO_EDGE unchanged, M=6, 0 excluded;
  synthetic SURVIVES, M=5, 24h HIGH excluded; selfcheck still PASS, first-survive a=0.35)
- README: document the guard in five-stages, flags, machine spec, reading-output
